#!perl
use strict;
use warnings;
use OptArgs qw/dispatch/;

dispatch(qw/run App::bifsync/);

__END__


=head1 NAME

bifsync - synchronization server for bif hubs

=head1 VERSION

0.1.0 (yyyy-mm-dd)

=head1 SYNOPSIS

  bifsync DIRECTORY

=head1 DESCRIPTION

Receive synchronization requests from bif clients.

Input is accepted on I<stdin>. Normal output is printed to I<stdout>.
Error messages are sent to I<stderr>.  Debugging information may go to
I<stderr> when F<DIRECTORY/debug> exists, otherwise information and
errors will be logged to the syslog.

An exit value of zero indicates success.

=head1 SEE ALSO

L<bif>(1)

